storing accesstoken on sever side:

Store the token in the server's session or database associated with the user's session or account. 
When the user is redirected to the destination, 
the server can retrieve the token and use it for authentication or authorization.

Example (Server-Side Storage and Redirect):
// Store the token in the server-side session or database
req.session.accessToken = accessToken;

// Server-side redirect to the welcome page
res.redirect("/welcome");

